CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 18, 1948, pg. 20, reads: "Duke Steps Out for Vets - Just before playing a concert in Pittsburgh, popular Duke Ellington dropped by the big Vets Hospital at Aspinwall, Pa., and strutted his stuff for the patients.  Here's Duke giving the 'duke' to some of his enthusiastic admirers."
TitMainTitle: Duke Ellington seated at edge of stage signing autographs for patients at Veteran's Hospital, Aspinwall
